definition.value: A mannotriose consisting of alpha-D-mannopyranose, beta-D-mannopyranose and D-mannopyranose residues joined in sequence by (1->3) and (1->4) glycosidic bonds.
A disaccharide that is alpha-D-galactopyranose in which the hydroxy group at position 2 has been converted into the corresponding beta-L-fucopyranoside.
An alpha-L-Fucp-(1->6)-D-Galp in which the carbon bearing the anomeric hydroxy group has beta configuration.
A galactotriose consisting of D-galactopyranose, alpha-D-galactopyranose and beta-D-galactopyranose residues joined in sequence by (1->4) glycosidic bonds.

A trisaccharide consisting of alpha-L-fucopyranose and beta-D-galactose residues joined by a (1->4) glycosidic bond in which the hydroxy group at position 3 of the galactopyranose ring has been converted into the corresponding beta-D-glucopyranosyl derivative.

A branched amino octasaccharide that consists of the linear tetrasaccharide beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-D-Glc in which the beta-D-Gal residue is substituted at position 6 by a beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc group. It is found in human milk.
An alpha-D-Glcp-(1->3)-D-Galp in which the carbon bearing the anomeric hydroxy group has beta configuration.
A beta-diketone that is pentane in which the hydrogens at positions 2 and 4 are replaced by oxo groups.
An amino disaccharide consisting of a beta-D-galactopyranose residue and two 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-beta-D-glucopyranose residues joined in sequence by (1->4) glycosidic bonds.
A 1-O-(D-glucosyl)glycerol in which the D-glucosyl moiety has alpha configuration at the anomeric centre.
